teMetadata`, `splitTestOnlyMetadata`, `fixTestNativeImageRun`, `addTestedVersion`, `fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`), reporting tasks (`jacocoTestReport`, `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `generateLibraryStats`, `analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess`), and the `package` release task. The full task reference lives in [DEVELOPING.md](DEVELOPING.md).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:251:- **NFR-2 Isolation.** Per-coordinate test execution must not depend on or affect other coordinates' build outputs.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:255:- **NFR-6 Sharded scalability.** Any Gradle task that accepts `-Pcoordinates=` must accept `k/n` shards so CI can parallelize. The harness must handle adding a new library without code changes (purely metadata-driven discovery).\n./forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:129:        issue_coordinates=\"org.example:lib:1.0.0\",\n./forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:148:            \"--coordinates\", \"org.example:lib:1.0.0\",\n./forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:971:        pipeline_argv = [\"--coordinates\", claimed_issue.issue_coordinates]\n./forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:979:                \"--coordinates\", claimed_issue.issue_coordinates,\n./forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:990:        pipeline_argv = [\"--coordinates\", claimed_issue.issue_coordinates]\n./forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:998:                \"--coordinates\", claimed_issue.issue_coordinates,\n./forge/tests/test_make_pr_not_for_native_image.py:74:                patch.object(make_pr_not_for_native_image, \"find_issue_for_coordinates\") as find_issue, \\\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:22:| Maven coordinate | `--coordinates group:artifact:version` | yes |\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:145:    TestLoop --> RunTest[run_test_command<br/>'./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=...']\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:218:./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=<g:a:v> --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar --metadataOutputDir=<output_dir>/agent\n./forge/